      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶  ¶ bot Garden ¶ 20/5/72 ¶  ¶ I think I have at last satisfactor[e]ly arranged about getting an other Todea, dear Dr Hooker. The season has been unusually wet; but if I can get it away next...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.05.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-1881, ff. 41-42.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Annotated ‘And Aug 10/72’.</p>
               </note>Melbourne<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/5/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I think I have at last satisfactor[e]ly arranged about getting an other Todea, dear Dr Hooker. The season has been unusually wet; but if I can get it away next month it will come still before winter to you, though it will have to encounter the frosts of Cape Horn. Should I fail to get such a monster, as you desire,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No specific request for additional<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Todea</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been found in Hooker's surviving letters, but see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>J. Hooker to M, 28 March 1870 (in this edition as 70-03-28b) and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>J. Hooker to M,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1 December 1871<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 71-12-01a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>then I will return the £15 - -, which are now fully at my disposal, as you generously and disinterestedly gave me alone for the sending of the other large specimen credit, which is really not just to yourself.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Booth who received the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Todea</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>specimen concerned also reimbursed £15 to Hooker: J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Booth to J. Hooker 26 June 1871<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as M71-06-26).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I admire much the record of this plant in your Magazine,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Botanical m</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">agazine</seg>, vol. 98, 1872, t. 5954.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but there is a slight alteration needed in one part of the record. These large Todeas do not emanate always<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">laterally</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from the banks of torrents or rivulets, but more frequently stand quite upright in the shallow water-courses, the rivulets washing around them and the Todeas standing in the water like so many little islands. I assure you the game of getting at one of these giants in the deep ravines and recesses in this colony at least is highly exciting. Shooting excursions or deer staking<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>stalking?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is nothing compared to it. Chamois hunting is a fairer comparison.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By way of trial I am going to send you a tall stem of Cycas angulata (C. gracilis Miq.) If it perishes on the way, it will still be acceptable for the Museum.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Poor Mrs Calvert, formerly Miss Atkinson, whose name so often occurs in the flor Australiana, died this month.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Louisa Calvert died<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>28 April 1872 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald</seg>, 30 April 1872, p. 1). The newspaper published an obituary on 2 May 1872, p. 7.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">In 1866 she had asked her lawyer to draft a will. Her instructions included</seg>:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5909in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">My collection of natural history sketches to go to Dr Ferdinand Mueller government Botanist at Melbourne.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5909in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">He has been a kind friend to me and would value them they might be useful in illustrating the natural history of the colony.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(L. Atkinson to N. Stenhouse, undated note, annotated as received on 11 October 1866; A100, p. 324, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.) That will if executed would have become void on her marriage in 1869, but she had given sketches to M before she died and M had sent them and her accompanying notes to Germany as possibly useful for display or publication; see M to F. von Krauss, 26 January 1871, and</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>W. Sonder to F. von Krauss, 9 June 1871 (in this edition as M71-06-09).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>She leaves an infant<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>child. Her husband is Jam.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Calvert Esq J.P. one of the Companions of Leichhardt in his first great Expedition, a truly excellent man.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Gardener, to whom you gave an introduction, has called; but in this country, any man, eve[r] so inferior, cannot be moved to make place for a better one. Hence I cannot give employment for your protegee however much I wish. I try to get him a place elsewhere.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>‘I try ... elsewhere’<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">marginal note with intended position indicated by *</seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>My miseries in the Department arose largely from the continued grossest secret misrepresentations of a few of the lowest underlings of gardeners, one particularly vulgar and low, and whom I cannot remove, though he holds only the place of a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">common working</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>gardener.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Smith? See D. Coller to M, 10 March 1866 and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>D. Coller to M,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>11 May 1870.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Yet withall I am held<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">responsible</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">welworking</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the department, but not supported in my authority!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The appendix to the Acclim. Soc. Report on utilitarian plant<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B72.13.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will only be printed in full by next mail, so my lecture on the objects of bot Gardens<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B72.07.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With best regards yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My reply to the stupid cruel and largely truthless report of the three [persons], who sat anno dei 1871 to judge on her Majestys bot Garden of Victoria, has not yet been printed;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn10" n="11">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For the reply see M to C Duffy, 6 February 1872. M later sent a manuscript copy to Kew<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(RGB, Kew Misc. Reports, Melbourne, Mueller).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>No contemporary published version of the full response has been found, but it is summarized in newspaper reports of a meeting between the Minister of Lands, M and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>William<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ferguson, e.g.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Daily t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">elegraph</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Melbourne), 12 July 1872, p. 3. See also Maroske<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Cohn (1996).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but when issued you surely shall have a copy. So you may see, what it means when proverbially it has become said "what may happen to a man in Victoria"</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cycas angulata</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cycas gracilis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Todea</p>
         </div>
      </body>
